        @* Administration section. Policy="identity.*.manage" gates were dropped
           in N7-x: those policies require a `scope` claim on the ClaimsPrincipal,
           but the cookie-based BFF flow stores the AT in AuthenticationProperties
           and does NOT project AT scopes onto user claims — so even an admin
           token would silently hide every link. Pages themselves still enforce
           [Authorize] and the management API enforces scope server-side, so
           unauthorised callers see a 403 from the call rather than a hidden link.
           See IDENTITY_WEB_REDESIGN_PLAN.md → "sidebar policy gates" for the
           full rationale. *@
        <AuthorizeView>
